Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced List Operations

Provides comprehensive list utilities with performance optimizations for AI systems requiring
efficient data manipulation, filtering, transformation, and analysis operations.

Advanced features include:
- Core list operations with proper error handling and bounds checking
- Functional programming utilities (map, filter, reduce) for data transformation
- Advanced slicing and indexing with negative index support
- Bulk operations and concatenation for efficient data processing
- Sorting algorithms with custom comparators and reverse ordering
- Search and analysis operations with predicate-based filtering
- Memory-efficient operations with proper copying strategies
- Production-ready error handling and edge case management
:End Note

Type ListOperationResult is Dictionary with:
    success as Boolean
    result as Any
    error_message as String

Note: Core List Creation and Modification

Process called "create_list" that takes elements as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Return elements

Process called "create_empty_list" that returns List[Any]:
    Return list containing

Process called "append" that takes lst as List[Any] and value as Any returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    Add value to result
    Return result

Process called "append_multiple" that takes lst as List[Any] and values as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    For each value in values:
        Add value to result
    Return result

Process called "insert_at_index" that takes lst as List[Any] and index as Integer and value as Any returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    If index is less than 0:
        Set index to length plus index
    If index is less than 0:
        Set index to 0
    If index is greater than length:
        Set index to length
    
    Let before be slice_list with lst as lst and start as 0 and end as index
    Let after be slice_list with lst as lst and start as index and end as length
    Let single_item_list be list containing value
    
    Return concatenate_lists with lst1 as before and lst2 as concatenate_lists with lst1 as single_item_list and lst2 as after

Process called "remove_at_index" that takes lst as List[Any] and index as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    If index is less than 0:
        Set index to length plus index
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length:
        Return lst
    
    Let before be slice_list with lst as lst and start as 0 and end as index
    Let after be slice_list with lst as lst and start as index plus 1 and end as length
    Return concatenate_lists with lst1 as before and lst2 as after

Process called "remove_value" that takes lst as List[Any] and value as Any returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If item is not equal to value:
            Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "remove_all" that takes lst as List[Any] and value as Any returns List[Any]:
    Return remove_value with lst as lst and value as value

Process called "pop" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Dictionary:
    Let length be length of lst
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return dictionary with:
            success as false
            result as lst
            value as None
            error_message as "Cannot pop from empty list"
    
    Let value be lst[length minus 1]
    Let new_list be slice_list with lst as lst and start as 0 and end as length minus 1
    
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        result as new_list
        value as value
        error_message as ""

Process called "pop_at_index" that takes lst as List[Any] and index as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let length be length of lst
    If index is less than 0:
        Set index to length plus index
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length:
        Return dictionary with:
            success as false
            result as lst
            value as None
            error_message as "Index out of bounds"
    
    Let value be lst[index]
    Let new_list be remove_at_index with lst as lst and index as index
    
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        result as new_list
        value as value
        error_message as ""

Process called "clear" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Return list containing

Process called "copy_list" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "deep_copy" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If item is List:
            Add deep_copy with lst as item to result
        Otherwise:
            Add item to result
    Return result

Note: Query and Analysis Operations

Process called "list_length" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Integer:
    Return length of lst

Process called "is_empty" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Boolean:
    Return length of lst is equal to 0

Process called "get" that takes lst as List[Any] and index as Integer returns Any:
    Let length be length of lst
    If index is less than 0:
        Set index to length plus index
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length:
        Return None
    Return lst[index]

Process called "get_safe" that takes lst as List[Any] and index as Integer and default as Any returns Any:
    Let length be length of lst
    If index is less than 0:
        Set index to length plus index
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length:
        Return default
    Return lst[index]

Process called "set" that takes lst as List[Any] and index as Integer and value as Any returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    If index is less than 0:
        Set index to length plus index
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length:
        Return lst
    
    Let result be list containing
    For i from 0 to length:
        If i is equal to index:
            Add value to result
        Otherwise:
            Add lst[i] to result
    Return result

Process called "contains" that takes lst as List[Any] and value as Any returns Boolean:
    For each item in lst:
        If item is equal to value:
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "count" that takes lst as List[Any] and value as Any returns Integer:
    Let count be 0
    For each item in lst:
        If item is equal to value:
            Set count to count plus 1
    Return count

Process called "index_of" that takes lst as List[Any] and value as Any returns Integer:
    For i from 0 to length of lst:
        If lst[i] is equal to value:
            Return i
    Return -1

Process called "index_of_safe" that takes lst as List[Any] and value as Any returns Dictionary:
    For i from 0 to length of lst:
        If lst[i] is equal to value:
            Return dictionary with:
                found as true
                index as i
    
    Return dictionary with:
        found as false
        index as -1

Note: Slicing and Indexing Operations

Process called "slice_list" that takes lst as List[Any] and start as Integer and end as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    If start is less than 0:
        Set start to length plus start
    If end is less than 0:
        Set end to length plus end
    If start is less than 0:
        Set start to 0
    If end is greater than length:
        Set end to length
    If start is greater than or equal to end:
        Return list containing
    
    Let result be list containing
    For i from start to end:
        Add lst[i] to result
    Return result

Process called "slice_with_step" that takes lst as List[Any] and start as Integer and end as Integer and step as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    If start is less than 0:
        Set start to length plus start
    If end is less than 0:
        Set end to length plus end
    If start is less than 0:
        Set start to 0
    If end is greater than length:
        Set end to length
    If step is equal to 0:
        Return list containing
    
    Let result be list containing
    If step is greater than 0:
        Let i be start
        While i is less than end:
            Add lst[i] to result
            Set i to i plus step
    Otherwise:
        Let i be start
        While i is greater than end:
            If i is greater than or equal to 0:
                Add lst[i] to result
            Set i to i plus step
    
    Return result

Process called "get_first" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Any:
    If length of lst is equal to 0:
        Return None
    Return lst[0]

Process called "get_last" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let length be length of lst
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return None
    Return lst[length minus 1]

Process called "get_first_safe" that takes lst as List[Any] and default as Any returns Any:
    If length of lst is equal to 0:
        Return default
    Return lst[0]

Process called "get_last_safe" that takes lst as List[Any] and default as Any returns Any:
    Let length be length of lst
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return default
    Return lst[length minus 1]

Note: Bulk Operations

Process called "extend" that takes lst as List[Any] and other as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Return concatenate_lists with lst1 as lst and lst2 as other

Process called "extend_multiple" that takes lst as List[Any] and others as List[List[Any]] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    For each other in others:
        Set result to concatenate_lists with lst1 as result and lst2 as other
    Return result

Process called "reverse" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    Let result be list containing
    For i from length minus 1 to 0 by -1:
        Add lst[i] to result
    Return result

Process called "reverse_in_place" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Return reverse with lst as lst

Note: Searching and Filtering Operations

Process called "find" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns Dictionary:
    For i from 0 to length of lst:
        If predicate with item as lst[i] is equal to true:
            Return dictionary with:
                found as true
                index as i
                value as lst[i]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        found as false
        index as -1
        value as None

Process called "find_all" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns List[Integer]:
    Let indices be list containing
    For i from 0 to length of lst:
        If predicate with item as lst[i] is equal to true:
            Add i to indices
    Return indices

Process called "filter" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If predicate with item as item is equal to true:
            Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "filter_not" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If predicate with item as item is equal to false:
            Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "take" that takes lst as List[Any] and n as Integer returns List[Any]:
    If n is less than or equal to 0:
        Return list containing
    Let length be length of lst
    If n is greater than or equal to length:
        Return copy_list with lst as lst
    Return slice_list with lst as lst and start as 0 and end as n

Process called "drop" that takes lst as List[Any] and n as Integer returns List[Any]:
    If n is less than or equal to 0:
        Return copy_list with lst as lst
    Let length be length of lst
    If n is greater than or equal to length:
        Return list containing
    Return slice_list with lst as lst and start as n and end as length

Process called "take_while" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If predicate with item as item is equal to true:
            Add item to result
        Otherwise:
            Break
    Return result

Process called "drop_while" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let start_index be 0
    For i from 0 to length of lst:
        If predicate with item as lst[i] is equal to true:
            Set start_index to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    Return slice_list with lst as lst and start as start_index and end as length of lst

Note: Transformation Operations

Process called "map" that takes lst as List[Any] and transform as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        Add transform with item as item to result
    Return result

Process called "map_with_index" that takes lst as List[Any] and transform as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For i from 0 to length of lst:
        Add transform with item as lst[i] and index as i to result
    Return result

Process called "flat_map" that takes lst as List[Any] and transform as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        Let transformed be transform with item as item
        For each sub_item in transformed:
            Add sub_item to result
    Return result

Process called "zip" that takes lst1 as List[Any] and lst2 as List[Any] returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let length1 be length of lst1
    Let length2 be length of lst2
    Let min_length be min_int with a as length1 and b as length2
    Let result be list containing
    
    For i from 0 to min_length:
        Add dictionary with:
            first as lst1[i]
            second as lst2[i]
        to result
    
    Return result

Process called "zip_longest" that takes lst1 as List[Any] and lst2 as List[Any] and fill_value as Any returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let length1 be length of lst1
    Let length2 be length of lst2
    Let max_length be max_int with a as length1 and b as length2
    Let result be list containing
    
    For i from 0 to max_length:
        Let item1 be get_safe with lst as lst1 and index as i and default as fill_value
        Let item2 be get_safe with lst as lst2 and index as i and default as fill_value
        Add dictionary with:
            first as item1
            second as item2
        to result
    
    Return result

Note: Sorting and Ordering Operations

Process called "sort" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    Return sort_in_place with lst as result

Process called "sort_in_place" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        For j from 0 to length minus i minus 1:
            If compare_values with a as lst[j] and b as lst[j plus 1] is greater than 0:
                Let temp be lst[j]
                Set lst[j] to lst[j plus 1]
                Set lst[j plus 1] to temp
    Return lst

Process called "sort_with_comparator" that takes lst as List[Any] and comparator as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    Return sort_in_place_with_comparator with lst as result and comparator as comparator

Process called "sort_in_place_with_comparator" that takes lst as List[Any] and comparator as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        For j from 0 to length minus i minus 1:
            If comparator with a as lst[j] and b as lst[j plus 1] is equal to true:
                Let temp be lst[j]
                Set lst[j] to lst[j plus 1]
                Set lst[j plus 1] to temp
    Return lst

Process called "sort_reverse" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    Return sort_in_place_reverse with lst as result

Process called "sort_in_place_reverse" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let length be length of lst
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        For j from 0 to length minus i minus 1:
            If compare_values with a as lst[j] and b as lst[j plus 1] is less than 0:
                Let temp be lst[j]
                Set lst[j] to lst[j plus 1]
                Set lst[j plus 1] to temp
    Return lst

Note: Utility Operations

Process called "unique" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let seen be dictionary with:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If item not in seen:
            Set seen[item] to true
            Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "unique_by" that takes lst as List[Any] and key_func as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let seen be dictionary with:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        Let key be key_func with item as item
        If key not in seen:
            Set seen[key] to true
            Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "flatten" that takes lst as List[List[Any]] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each sublist in lst:
        For each item in sublist:
            Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "flatten_deep" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If item is List:
            Let flattened be flatten_deep with lst as item
            For each sub_item in flattened:
                Add sub_item to result
        Otherwise:
            Add item to result
    Return result

Process called "chunk" that takes lst as List[Any] and size as Integer returns List[List[Any]]:
    If size is less than or equal to 0:
        Return list containing
    
    Let result be list containing
    Let length be length of lst
    For i from 0 to length by size:
        Let chunk_end be min_int with a as i plus size and b as length
        Let chunk be slice_list with lst as lst and start as i and end as chunk_end
        Add chunk to result
    Return result

Process called "partition" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns Dictionary:
    Let true_list be list containing
    Let false_list be list containing
    For each item in lst:
        If predicate with item as item is equal to true:
            Add item to true_list
        Otherwise:
            Add item to false_list
    
    Return dictionary with:
        true_items as true_list
        false_items as false_list

Process called "group_by" that takes lst as List[Any] and key_func as Process returns Dictionary[Any, List[Any]]:
    Let groups be dictionary with:
    For each item in lst:
        Let key be key_func with item as item
        If key in groups:
            Add item to groups[key]
        Otherwise:
            Let single_item_list be list containing item
            Set groups[key] to single_item_list
    Return groups

Process called "all" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns Boolean:
    For each item in lst:
        If predicate with item as item is equal to false:
            Return false
    Return true

Process called "any" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns Boolean:
    For each item in lst:
        If predicate with item as item is equal to true:
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "none" that takes lst as List[Any] and predicate as Process returns Boolean:
    For each item in lst:
        If predicate with item as item is equal to true:
            Return false
    Return true

Process called "sum" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Float:
    Let total be 0.0
    For each item in lst:
        If item is Integer:
            Set total to total plus item as Float
        Otherwise if item is Float:
            Set total to total plus item
    Return total

Process called "product" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Float:
    Let total be 1.0
    For each item in lst:
        If item is Integer:
            Set total to total multiplied by item as Float
        Otherwise if item is Float:
            Set total to total multiplied by item
    Return total

Process called "average" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Float:
    Let length be length of lst
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    Return sum with lst as lst divided by length as Float

Process called "min_list" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Any:
    If length of lst is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let min_val be lst[0]
    For each item in lst:
        If compare_values with a as item and b as min_val is less than 0:
            Set min_val to item
    Return min_val

Process called "max_list" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Any:
    If length of lst is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let max_val be lst[0]
    For each item in lst:
        If compare_values with a as item and b as max_val is greater than 0:
            Set max_val to item
    Return max_val

Process called "min_by" that takes lst as List[Any] and key_func as Process returns Any:
    If length of lst is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let min_item be lst[0]
    Let min_key be key_func with item as min_item
    
    For each item in lst:
        Let item_key be key_func with item as item
        If compare_values with a as item_key and b as min_key is less than 0:
            Set min_item to item
            Set min_key to item_key
    
    Return min_item

Process called "max_by" that takes lst as List[Any] and key_func as Process returns Any:
    If length of lst is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let max_item be lst[0]
    Let max_key be key_func with item as max_item
    
    For each item in lst:
        Let item_key be key_func with item as item
        If compare_values with a as item_key and b as max_key is greater than 0:
            Set max_item to item
            Set max_key to item_key
    
    Return max_item

Process called "reduce" that takes lst as List[Any] and reducer as Process and initial as Any returns Any:
    Let accumulator be initial
    For each item in lst:
        Set accumulator to reducer with acc as accumulator and item as item
    Return accumulator

Process called "fold_left" that takes lst as List[Any] and reducer as Process and initial as Any returns Any:
    Return reduce with lst as lst and reducer as reducer and initial as initial

Process called "fold_right" that takes lst as List[Any] and reducer as Process and initial as Any returns Any:
    Let reversed_list be reverse with lst as lst
    Return reduce with lst as reversed_list and reducer as reducer and initial as initial

Process called "scan" that takes lst as List[Any] and reducer as Process and initial as Any returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing initial
    Let accumulator be initial
    
    For each item in lst:
        Set accumulator to reducer with acc as accumulator and item as item
        Add accumulator to result
    
    Return result

Process called "list_statistics" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let stats be dictionary with:
    
    Set stats["length"] to length of lst
    Set stats["is_empty"] to is_empty with lst as lst
    
    If length of lst is greater than 0:
        Set stats["first"] to get_first with lst as lst
        Set stats["last"] to get_last with lst as lst
        
        Let numeric_items be filter with lst as lst and predicate as is_numeric_value
        If length of numeric_items is greater than 0:
            Set stats["sum"] to sum with lst as numeric_items
            Set stats["average"] to average with lst as numeric_items
            Set stats["min"] to min_list with lst as numeric_items
            Set stats["max"] to max_list with lst as numeric_items
        Otherwise:
            Set stats["sum"] to 0.0
            Set stats["average"] to 0.0
            Set stats["min"] to None
            Set stats["max"] to None
        
        Set stats["unique_count"] to length of unique with lst as lst
    Otherwise:
        Set stats["first"] to None
        Set stats["last"] to None
        Set stats["sum"] to 0.0
        Set stats["average"] to 0.0
        Set stats["min"] to None
        Set stats["max"] to None
        Set stats["unique_count"] to 0
    
    Return stats

Process called "concatenate_lists" that takes lst1 as List[Any] and lst2 as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    
    For each item in lst1:
        Add item to result
    
    For each item in lst2:
        Add item to result
    
    Return result

Process called "compare_values" that takes a as Any and b as Any returns Integer:
    If a is Integer and b is Integer:
        If a is less than b:
            Return -1
        Otherwise if a is greater than b:
            Return 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
    Otherwise if a is Float and b is Float:
        If a is less than b:
            Return -1
        Otherwise if a is greater than b:
            Return 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
    Otherwise if a is String and b is String:
        If a is less than b:
            Return -1
        Otherwise if a is greater than b:
            Return 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
    Otherwise:
        Return 0

Process called "min_int" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Otherwise:
        Return b

Process called "max_int" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return a
    Otherwise:
        Return b

Process called "is_numeric_value" that takes item as Any returns Boolean:
    Return item is Integer or item is Float